# /assets/ — manual placement folder

This folder is where Iván drops static assets the site references.

## Required file

| Filename | Purpose | Specs |
|---|---|---|
| `ivan-tamayo-ramos.jpg` | Profile photo (used by JSON-LD `image` and `og:image`) | JPG; ≥1200×630 px; ideally 1:1 or 5:4 aspect, square-ish portrait; under 500 KB; sRGB color space |

## How to source it (recommended)

1. Open your LinkedIn profile (`linkedin.com/in/ivan-tamayo-ramos-099a3255/`).
2. Click your profile photo → "Download original photo" (LinkedIn's full-resolution export).
3. If LinkedIn does not let you download original, open the photo in a new tab, right-click, "Save image as…".
4. Rename the file exactly to `ivan-tamayo-ramos.jpg`.
5. (Optional) Re-encode at quality 85 to keep file size under 500 KB. macOS: open in Preview → File → Export → JPEG, quality 85. Windows: Photos app or any image editor.
6. Drop the file in this folder.

## After placement

No further action needed. The site references `/assets/ivan-tamayo-ramos.jpg` at:
- `about.html` JSON-LD `image` field
- `index.html` JSON-LD `image` field
- `schema_org_person.json` `image` field
- (no `<img>` tag in HTML body — the photo currently only ships as structured-data metadata, which is what AI crawlers ingest)

If you want the photo also displayed visibly on the home or about page, reply "show photo on site" and I add an `<img>` tag in the appropriate place with the right styling for the classical aesthetic.
